Female.description: The huge, crow-sized Ringed Kingfisher is a tropical species that barely extends its range into Texas. It is considerably larger and stouter than Belted Kingfishers, with a truly massive bill and almost entirely rusty underparts.

Male.description: Green Kingfishers occur in south Texas and occasionally Arizona. They are about half the size of a Belted Kingfisher, although with a disproportionately long bill. Their green-and-white plumage is distinctive if seen in good light.
